Return only the corrected Java rule method body.
Keep the intended business semantics unchanged and fix syntax, type, or facade API usage errors.
Do not include package, imports, class declarations, annotations, method declarations,
markdown, or explanations.

Use only APIs that compile in ModuleAlgBase and match the SDK profile.

When SDK profile is POST:
- Use POST instance-view APIs only: currentInst(), parameter(code), part(code),
  partCategory(code), partCategorySum(code), value(), setValue(...), dynAttr(...),
  setDynAttr(...), sumQuantity(), and sumDynAttr4Int(...).
- For numeric writeback to parameters, wrap numeric values with String.valueOf(...).
- For category-scoped parameter writeback, use partCategory("categoryCode").parameter("paraCode").setValue(...).
- For category-scoped part writeback, use partCategory("categoryCode").part("partCode").setQuantity(...)
  or partCategory("categoryCode").part("partCode").setDynAttr(...).
- Use partCategory("categoryCode").sumQuantity() for category quantity totals.
- Use partCategorySum("categoryCode") only for dynamic-attribute aggregation such as
  sumDynAttr4Int("attrCode"), dynAttr("attrCode"), or dynAttrs("attrCode").
  Do not call partCategorySum("categoryCode").sumQuantity() or .quantity().
- Do not use constraint-model APIs such as model(), para(...), partVar(...),
  partCategoryVar(...), onlyEnforceIf(...), addLessOrEqual(...), inCompatible(...),
  addCompatibleConstraint..., or updatePriorityObjectFuntion(...).

When SDK profile is CONSTRAINT:
- Category counts: model().sum4Selected("categoryCode", "", "optional Attr=value filter").
- Category quantities: model().sum4Quantity("categoryCode", "", "optional Attr=value filter").
- Aggregate weighted dynamic-attribute totals:
  model().sum4Quantity("categoryCodeOrCommaSeparatedCodes", "attrCode", "optional Attr=value filter").
- The attrCode argument is a numeric weighting attribute, not a filter attribute. For selected-count rules,
  use attrCode "" and put attribute predicates in the filter condition. For total part quantity rules,
  also use attrCode "" unless the rule says weighted by a numeric dynamic attribute.
- Cross-category aggregate totals use comma-separated category codes in the first argument.
- Product-level aggregate totals over all instances of a multi-instance category use categoryCode* in the
  first argument.
- Do not add * only because a category supports multi-instance; use * only when the natural language explicitly
  asks for all instances of that category.
- Do not mix * and comma-separated categories in one aggregate call, such as "disk*,mainBoard".
  If a true rule needs all instances of one category plus another category, build separate aggregate
  expressions and combine them with model().newPartLinearExpr(...).addExpr(...).
- Part-category rules, including effectScope=AllInst rules, should use two-argument overloads such as
  model().sum4Quantity("attrCode", "filter") and model().sum4Selected("attrCode", "filter") for that
  category context.
- Do not enumerate atomic parts with partVar(...).quantityVar() to build aggregate or weighted totals.
- In filter conditions, use dynamic attribute values from context dynAttr or option codeValue, not option codes.
- Filter conditions are rule-engine strings such as Attr=value or Attr>=number; do not use Java == and do
  not quote string values inside the filter.
- Numeric constraints: model().addLessOrEqual(...), model().addGreaterOrEqual(...),
  or model().addEquality(...).
- Parameter compatibility: addCompatibleConstraintRequires(ruleCode, leftPara, listOf("leftOption"),
  rightPara, listOf("rightOption")), addCompatibleConstraintInCompatible(...),
  or addCompatibleConstraintCoDependent(...).
- Direct expressions: para("p1").valueVar(), para("p1").option("optionCode").selectedVar(),
  partVar("part1").quantityVar(), partVar("part1").hiddenVar(), model().newBoolVar(...),
  and onlyEnforceIf(...).
- Linear expression terms: AlgCPLinearExpr.addTerm and PartAlgCPLinearExpr.addTerm use
  addTerm(variable, coefficient), such as expr.addTerm(para("p1").valueVar(), 1). Do not reverse
  the arguments.
- To combine aggregate PartAlgCPLinearExpr values such as model().sum4Quantity(...) or
  model().sum4Selected(...), use compositeExpr.addExpr(aggregateExpr, coefficient).
  Do not pass aggregate expressions to addTerm(...).
- PartAlgCPLinearExpr is also a linear expression. It can be used in numeric constraints such as
  model().addGreaterOrEqual(totalExpr, 0), model().addLessOrEqual(totalExpr, limit), or
  model().addGreaterOrEqual(totalExpr, para("p1").valueVar()). When comparing an aggregate expression
  with a parameter, use para("p1").valueVar(), not the ParaVar itself.
- model().addBoolAnd and model().addBoolOr accept exactly one AlgCPLiteral[] argument.
  To bind a BoolVar to a conjunction, use model().addBoolAnd(new AlgCPLiteral[] {a, b}).onlyEnforceIf(cond)
  and model().addBoolOr(new AlgCPLiteral[] {a.not(), b.not()}).onlyEnforceIf(cond.not()).
  To bind a BoolVar to a disjunction, use model().addBoolOr(new AlgCPLiteral[] {a, b}).onlyEnforceIf(cond)
  and model().addBoolAnd(new AlgCPLiteral[] {a.not(), b.not()}).onlyEnforceIf(cond.not()).
  Do not call model().addBoolAnd(cond, a, b) or model().addBoolOr(cond, a, b).
- model().addEquality(...), model().addDifferent(...), model().addLessOrEqual(...),
  model().addGreaterOrEqual(...), and similar numeric APIs return AlgCPConstraint, not AlgCPLiteral.
  Never put those calls inside AlgCPLiteral[] and never pass them to model().addImplication(...).
- To use a numeric predicate as a boolean literal, first create an AlgCPBoolVar and bind both directions:
  model().addEquality(expr, value).onlyEnforceIf(eqVar);
  model().addDifferent(expr, value).onlyEnforceIf(eqVar.not());
- model().addImplication(left, right) accepts AlgCPLiteral arguments only, such as BoolVar,
  hiddenVar(), option(...).selectedVar(), or their .not() forms.
- Hidden helper signature: use addVarAboutHiddenConstraints(para("p1"), para("p2")) for ParaVar values
  or addVarAboutHiddenConstraints(partVar("part1"), partVar("part2")) for PartVar values. It is a direct
  ModuleAlgBase method, not a model() method. Do not pass ruleCode, hiddenVar(), valueVar(), or BoolVar.
- If a rule can hide a parameter or part, call addVarAboutHiddenConstraints(...) for every parameter
  or part whose hiddenVar() is controlled by the rule. Without this registration, the engine adds
  default visible constraints and hidden solutions can become impossible.
- Priority constraints should be normal numeric constraints. Build a separate PartAlgCPLinearExpr for
  the objective, use model().newPartLinearExpr("name"), addExpr(...) for aggregate expressions,
  model().setObjectExpr(expr), and
  updatePriorityObjectFuntion(ruleCode, expr).
- Incompatibility: inCompatible(ruleCode, "category:Attr=value", "category:Attr=value").
Do not use partCategoryVar(...).count(), totalQuantityVariable(), selectedCount(),
model().addConstraint(...), addCompatibleConstraintInCompatible(partVar(...), partVar(...)),
inCompatible(partVar(...), partVar(...)), aggregate expressions built by enumerating partVar(...),
or POST instance-view APIs such as parameter(...).setValue(...), partCategorySum(...),
part(...), or partCategory(...).
